A home to early Larry Heard & Frankie Knuckles productions, Gherkin Records was one of the most influential House imprints in the late 80s. Brett Wilcots and Jim Stivers distributed a huge number of stone-cold classics from a pretty exhaustive list of of house & techno legends, before the operation wrapped up abruptly in 1991.
Finn McCorry selects an hour of records from the labels near-perfect core catalogue - a wealth of dreamy vocal cuts and a slew of early acid house experiments from Larry Heard under his Gherkin Jerks alias.

nts1.n: GHOST NOTES WORLDWIDE W/ Impey & Kamran
nts1.d: Tune into Ghost Notes Worldwide for that post-twilight sound. Night time music of all strains, with blunted R&B and hip hop instrumentals, neo-downtempo productions, slow jams, and hazy dancefloor sounds.

nts1.n: Hell Of A Club - You Make Me Feel So Good
nts1.d: Unapologetic theme night with the Fatale association…

Cherrystones - musician, international DJ, soundtrack composer, compiler and multi-genre music fiend - within his longstanding NTS shows Cherrystones showcases his inspirations, his passions and his listening habits as a sonic moodboard pooled from his revered archive encompassing the past, present and future sounds to soothe and challenge in equal measure. Photography Credit: Meghan Desmond
From the host: "A myriad of styles including psychedelic rock, rap.noise & beyond "

nts2.d: A North African tribute to the best football tournament.
Your monthly dose of curated sounds from the world of movie soundtracks with actress Agathe Rousselle.

SMUT Press is a print-publishing project founded by Jordan Hearns & Jack Scollard in 2022, based between Dublin and London. For NTS, SMUT Press will explore the relationships between nightlife, independent publishing and artistic communities through a variety of guests, discussions and musical dissections.
From the host: "Leeds based artist Sam Hutchinson joins us to trace his musical history. We discuss his origins in Sunderland’s punk/skate scenes, his time at Leeds Uni & School of the Damned, as well as his publishing work with Village Books and his own imprint BOOT."

Georgia are Justin Tripp and Brian Close - and they make music, videos, films and performances from their base in Chinatown, New York. Tune in for a monthly hour of oddball electronics; whether ambient or fit for the floor…

nts2.n: AUTOTUNE THE WORLD W/ CHRISTOPHER KIRKLEY
nts2.d:
International portal for contemporary pop, leaning into the autotuned future… from the mind of Christopher Kirkley, the mastermind behind record label Sahel Sounds.
From the host: "Kilalaky music from rural West Madagascar. Hi-energy percussive driven studio hits from 2007 - 2024."

nts2.n: RICH & JONNY PRESENT INZANE MICHIGAN - BLACK MERDA
nts2.d: Join John Olson (aka Inzane Johnny, of Wolf Eyes) and music writer Rich Tupica as they mine deep into Michigan's wilderness of sounds. No private press rarity is off limits: soul, gospel, oddities, punk, experimental, rockabilly, and garage rock. It's all unearthed. Strap in for an insanely bizarre ride across the Great Lakes State.

Sacred Pools is a monthly show, rotating between DJ October, Faso and Toshiki Ohta. All three hosts showcase a varied and intriguing combination of music on the Sacred Pools show - from harshly metallic noise rock, unhinged post-punk, chillingly minimal synth, breakbeat rave and pervy wedding disco.
From the host: "Keeping it slowfast for the first show of the year with a wander through Deutsch post-rock, a variety of rhythm workouts, sapphic downtempo, and a touch of fretless fusion at the end. Stay cozy, everyone

nts2.n: Tragic Magic w/ Mary Lattimore & Julianna Barwick
nts2.d: The celebrated composers Julianna Barwick & Mary Lattimore come together for Tragic Magic - their latest collaborative release. Heralded by three special guest radio shows recorded from our LA studio.

nts2.n: DARK ENTRIES: Perry Bamonte Tribute w/ Josh Cheon
nts2.d:
Dark Entries reissues archival and contemporary gems that prove to be crucial to our modern idea of bodily music that exists out of time. Electro, italo, cold wave, new beat, house, techno from a one-of-a-kind digger who visits dusty basements to rescue lost tapes.
From the host: "Tribute to Perry Bamonte of The Cure"
Piper Durabo AKA Maraschino serves up an assortment of hyperdelic jams from her NYC HQ

nts2.n: Carlos René: Te amaré hoy y mañana - Latin Funk & Disco
nts2.d:
Join us for monthly sessions with Carlos René, co-founder of Casa Calypso record shop in Mexico City. Carlos specializes in uncovering rare Latin American recordings and has a passion for a diverse range of genres, including cumbia, Latin funk, Mexican garage rock & psych, boogaloo, and other rare grooves. Let Carlos take you on a captivating musical journey through the vibrant sounds of Latin America that will keep you grooving any time of the day.
From the host: "Latin funk to shake off the winter chill. Just deep grooves, heavy bass, and a lot of attitude"

subtle.n: Collectors' Cuts w/ Antek feat. Ben Boe

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

ixxi and Fei take you on a percussive journey with their show syncop8, moving from downtempo ambient to breaks, polyrhythms, and high energy beats, exploring every rhythmic and textural nuance in between.
Representing UK Bass Music Culture across a range of styles, sounds and tempos.

Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
